              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Two PILOT-U plastic scintillators mounted on",
                " RCA 8575 phototubes separated by flight paths of",
                " 2.5-5.0m in air."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "NAICR"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " A conically shaped NaI detector (10.2cm thick)",
                " with a 6.9mg/cm2 Al entrance window was used for",
                " particle identification.",
                "Solid angle was defined by requiring a signal from",
                " two 1000 mu-m thick Si detectors (400mm2 areas)",
                " stacked in front of the NaI detector."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ERR-ANALYS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "E-ERR",
                "minimum_value": null,
                "maximum_value": null,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Energy uncertainty due to timing resolution;",
                " read from graphs."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "DATA-ERR",
                "minimum_value": null,
                "maximum_value": null,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Uncertainty in absolute cross sections for",
                " each angle independently. The small solid angles and",
                " the large range of data measured in this experiment",
                " required that somewhat larger count rates and less",
                " than optimal beam conditions be accepted in order to",
                " obtain satisfactory statistics for high-energy events."
              ]
            },
